🚀 2. SPACE RACE ACADEMY CURRICULUM

A full training pipeline for kids: Beginner → Intermediate → Advanced → Pre‑Olympic.

---

OVERVIEW

The Space Race Academy (SRA) is a multi‑tiered educational program that teaches children the fundamentals of piloting, physics, teamwork, and emotional regulation through safe, playful simulation.

---

TIER 1 — BEGINNER (Ages 6–9)

Goals

• Build confidence
• Learn basic controls
• Understand simple physics
• Practice teamwork


Modules

• Steering & braking
• Safe bumping
• Thermal hide‑and‑seek
• Camouflage tag
• “Hot Spot scramble”
• Emotional cooldown breaks


Skills Earned

• Spatial awareness
• Reaction timing
• Cooperation
• Basic thermal vision interpretation


---

TIER 2 — INTERMEDIATE (Ages 9–12)

Goals

• Introduce real physics
• Improve precision
• Teach problem‑solving


Modules

• Obstacle navigation
• Time trials
• Energy management basics
• Heat signature tracking
• Intro to orbital mechanics (kid‑friendly)


Skills Earned

• Predictive movement
• Basic mission planning
• Understanding thrust vs. drag
• Team strategy


---

TIER 3 — ADVANCED (Ages 12–15)

Goals

• Prepare for complex simulations
• Teach discipline and focus
• Introduce real aerospace concepts


Modules

• Zero‑G simulation
• Docking practice
• Thermal regulation challenges
• Multi‑phase mission runs
• “Shadow Race” against recorded pros


Skills Earned

• Precision piloting
• Heat management
• Advanced teamwork
• Emotional regulation under pressure


---

TIER 4 — PRE‑OLYMPIC (Ages 15–17)

Goals

• Prepare for future professional training
• Teach ethics, safety, and stewardship
• Build leadership


Modules

• Full orbital track simulations
• Emergency override drills
• Systems management
• Race strategy
• Steward’s Oath training
• Environmental ethics


Skills Earned

• High‑level piloting
• Mission command
• Safety-first mindset
• Leadership and mentorship


---

GRADUATION

Students receive the Space Steward Certificate, qualifying them for:

• Advanced aerospace programs
• Future SRO professional training
• STEM scholarships
• Mentorship roles for younger cadets


